19:19.844 --> 19:23.207
It was a look of hope, of promise, and of a future.

19:23.247 --> 19:28.212
It was on that vision tour that it felt like God gave me a glimpse through his eyes.

19:28.953 --> 19:30.354
Beautifully broke my heart.

19:30.690 --> 19:31.671
and planted a seed in me.

19:32.693 --> 19:37.360
When I returned home, I hung some of the pictures in our hallway of Abraham and others, so I would never forget.

19:37.380 --> 19:48.896
And for the next couple of years, I would regularly stop in front of those pictures and begin to weep, thinking about that little, beggar boy, and ask the question, God, why did you let me experience that?

19:49.237 --> 19:50.318
And what do you want me to do with it?

19:51.240 --> 19:58.290
I had often heard about stewarding our resources, our time, our money, our talents, but I had this recurring thought that I couldn't shake.

19:58.818 --> 20:00.900
How do I steward my experience?

20:01.801 --> 20:03.763
What do you want me to do, Lord, with what I encountered?

20:05.144 --> 20:12.971
I've heard it said that when you have something that makes you weak, it's always good to pay attention and to lean in, for it might be a space where God wants to use you.

20:14.313 --> 20:18.977
Sponsoring children with compassion became a family tradition, as each of our sons chose a child their own age.

20:19.578 --> 20:28.626
Years later, we traveled to El Salvador to visit the new Calvary Church plant in one part of the country, and also to meet our son, Hayden's sponsor child, Jeremiah's, and another part of El Salvador.

20:29.026 --> 20:33.873
There, our sons saw the impact of sponsorship, and I was instantly reminded of Ethiopia.

20:34.834 --> 20:47.311
Back at the church property of Calvary and Susal, we stood on the land that we were about to dedicate, and Duknay dreamed aloud, what if, what if one day this church could have its own compassion program?

20:47.712 --> 20:50.836
And Calvary back home could sponsor the children and send teams to visit.

20:51.797 --> 20:54.681
And that's where the seed planted years earlier began to grow.

20:55.402 --> 20:58.226
After years of faithful work by the team at Calvary and Susal,

20:58.498 --> 20:59.900
that dream became reality.

21:00.421 --> 21:05.770
It was 2022, 10 years later, that we hosted Compassion Sunday here at all of our campuses.

21:06.611 --> 21:10.297
But this time, every child sponsored was at one of our own compassion sites.

21:10.698 --> 21:14.544
Because God didn't just open a door in El Salvador, he also opened another in Mexico.

21:15.085 --> 21:23.659
And I'll never forget that weekend, watching all of our campuses respond with such generosity, sponsoring every single child at both sites.

21:24.360 --> 21:25.522
I had the honor and privilege of

21:25.762 --> 21:29.407
The very first child enrolled in the project, it was a little girl named Carito.

21:30.088 --> 21:40.962
When we flew down for the grand opening and finally met her, I'll never forget the look and the eyes of those families, evidence of the transformation that only the gospel of Jesus can bring to a community.

21:42.003 --> 21:48.191
And now every year, we lead trips to N.C. Sal, taking a team of cavalry women who come to lead outreaches to the families we serve there.

21:48.832 --> 21:53.618
These trips don't just change the lives of the kids and families we serve, they change us.

21:54.242 --> 22:00.530
They make us more like Jesus as we're confronted with poverty, with injustice, and the overwhelming needs of the poor.

22:01.512 --> 22:05.417
Being in the middle of the work of God that he's doing is the best place we can ever be.

22:06.438 --> 22:13.107
So this past August, just two months ago, our incredible mission team of Calvary women went to end Sosel, and it was on the opening night of worship.

22:13.328 --> 22:14.870
Carito, she's now nine years old.

22:15.871 --> 22:21.999
She ran over, she sat next to me, and she leaned over, and she said, Sosela, this is my favorite song.

22:22.440 --> 22:23.922
We were singing what a beautiful name.

22:24.162 --> 22:27.686
And at that moment, she just sang at the top of her lungs.

22:32.272 --> 22:35.396
This beautiful little girl singing about her love for Jesus.

22:36.598 --> 22:38.700
I just sat there and began to weep at the goodness of God.

22:38.740 --> 22:45.149
For me, it was a full circle moment because it had been 18 years since that first call to go to Ethiopia.

22:45.970 --> 22:52.658
And through the people we met and the burden the Holy Spirit put on hearts, it all led to this very moment because this is our God.

22:53.186 --> 22:55.390
a God of all nations who goes after the one.

22:56.251 --> 23:00.759
And for me, it was a young girl named Karita who's singing the same song I was singing.

23:01.360 --> 23:03.965
What a beautiful name it is, the name of Jesus.

23:04.946 --> 23:12.459
And so Calvary, I want to encourage you, pay attention to the burdens God places in your hearts and the dreams he puts in your minds.

23:13.461 --> 23:14.322
They're not an accident.

23:14.863 --> 23:18.770
They're an invitation to join the mission of God wherever it will take you.

23:19.618 --> 23:23.102
God doesn't need any of us to accomplish this mission, or just ordinary people.

23:23.723 --> 23:29.810
But it is a holy privilege to join him in the great adventure of bringing the good news of Jesus to the nations.

23:38.620 --> 23:39.621
I love that girl.

23:43.666 --> 23:46.930
It's such a privilege.

23:48.546 --> 23:53.432
to be able to experience the grace and love of God, because he came after all of us.

23:54.453 --> 24:02.984
When we did not have hope, when we did not have light, when we did not know the way up, it's such a privilege to be able to not just receive the love of God, but to pass it on to someone else.

24:04.085 --> 24:08.491
And this is what the church has the holy privilege to do, go and make disciples.

24:08.511 --> 24:14.418
Jesus does not need us, but he wants us to experience the joy of seeing

24:14.658 --> 24:17.662
people's lives come back to life, that transformation.

24:17.702 --> 24:21.127
There is no greater adventure in your life than following Jesus.

24:21.208 --> 24:24.913
And so pay attention to the burdens, pay attention to the experiences.

24:26.335 --> 24:33.486
One of the men and women that God used to plant seven or eight churches in Mexico and a bunch of different schools and then that rippled out to other places.

24:33.506 --> 24:34.928
This is a man named Robert Aguio.

24:34.988 --> 24:36.530
Robert was from Mexico.

24:36.994 --> 24:41.920
And he came here, I met him in the early 2000s, very involved in the leadership of this church and his wife and the school.

24:42.020 --> 24:43.823
And we went on a mission trip to Romania.

24:43.883 --> 24:46.526
And he was growing in such beautiful ways here.

24:46.566 --> 24:48.849
And then this question, who will go?

24:48.869 --> 24:52.353
And this bird in the god Plasin to go back to Mexico.

24:52.373 --> 24:59.282
And I want you to watch Robert's story to see again how God works through ordinary people filled with a spirit to go and change the world.

25:09.954 --> 25:12.197
Even though I grew up in Mexico, I wasn't born here.

25:12.217 --> 25:15.360
I lived in a couple of cities and ended up in Mexico City.

25:16.041 --> 25:20.026
And that's kind of the place where I first remember growing up.

25:20.046 --> 25:30.158
As I was growing up, my dream was always to go and live in the U.S. Ended up in the last two years of high school, was then boarding school in the U.S. And then from there went to the university.

25:30.198 --> 25:32.181
And pretty much I was there.

25:32.301 --> 25:36.626
That's where I was going to be and continue the rest of my life.

25:37.282 --> 25:40.427
I actually came to know Calvary Chapel in Florida.

25:40.447 --> 25:41.609
Somebody invited me to church.

25:41.649 --> 25:47.318
After being in the different churches, for me, it was like, this is what I would have been looking for.

25:47.378 --> 25:51.084
And the next year, I was offered a job to come in to work at CCA.

25:51.104 --> 25:52.526
It was the year three of CCA.

25:52.646 --> 25:53.708
And there we felt at home.

25:53.808 --> 25:55.631
This was a place where we were supposed to be.

25:55.651 --> 25:58.936
I was working in the evil's nest.

25:59.597 --> 26:03.864
Robert was just growing in his role as an administrator.

26:04.004 --> 26:05.426
He loved his job.

26:06.402 --> 26:07.323
We have a good life.

26:08.084 --> 26:08.745
We have a house.

26:08.945 --> 26:11.448
The kids are doing well at school.

26:12.290 --> 26:14.492
Somebody asked me, where do you see or something next five years?

26:14.512 --> 26:15.434
I was like, oh, here.

26:15.574 --> 26:18.057
I see my, you know, this was a place I wanted to be.

26:18.377 --> 26:24.385
He was required to teach a missions class, not to be, to be a missionary.

26:25.086 --> 26:27.689
That was not the, his idea.

26:28.090 --> 26:30.413
But, you know, the Lord had other plans.

26:31.234 --> 26:34.578
And he comes home and he, and he tells me, we need to talk.

26:35.298 --> 26:40.044
And that's when he told me, and I think the Lord's calling us to go to Mexico.

26:40.906 --> 26:43.669
The Lord put on my heart to come back and start a Christian school.

26:44.110 --> 26:47.975
He reminded me of the need there was for Christian education in Mexico.

26:48.756 --> 27:02.194
The Lord really began to speak to my heart and saying, you know, this is the reason that you, you know, since grew up in Mexico, I've given you the language, you know, the culture, you know, the people, you know, you can go back and

27:02.690 --> 27:08.458
do the things that you've been taught, the things that you've learned, and put them into practice in Mexico.

27:08.899 --> 27:13.205
Something like CCA in Mexico was kind of my goal.

27:14.907 --> 27:19.935
So we began looking at different cities, and Merida was one of the ones that I remembered.

27:19.955 --> 27:21.457
I'd actually never been there before.

27:21.917 --> 27:23.860
And then I said, I wonder if there's a Calvary Chapel there.

27:24.301 --> 27:28.186
So I put Calvary Chapel, Merida, and I popped the Calvary Chapel that's here.

27:28.226 --> 27:30.770
One of the last things on the web page

27:31.586 --> 27:36.894
as prayer requests was to start a Christian school in the next two years.

27:37.275 --> 27:38.937
That was that pastor's prayer request.

27:39.418 --> 27:44.205
So to us, that was like the confirmation like this is the place.

27:44.385 --> 27:46.108
This is where the Lord wants us.

27:47.770 --> 27:52.617
But we actually never looked anywhere after that, after we saw that and this is where we're at now.

27:53.699 --> 28:01.010
The influence to school system here in Mexico has from the education is more of a kind of a liberal

28:01.250 --> 28:03.612
more of a Marxist influence in there.

28:04.373 --> 28:12.581
So we saw the need and we started with teaching the word and teaching education through that biblical lens.

28:13.342 --> 28:16.905
First year, year one, 2006, we started with six and it was 12.

28:18.046 --> 28:23.932
Around year three and four, school just started growing, like it just exploded.

28:26.695 --> 28:29.938
So this is kind of the area where the school was.

28:30.466 --> 28:35.213
The building that we bought was kind of where that entrance is over there.

28:35.353 --> 28:35.994
You can't see it.

28:36.154 --> 28:41.281
And then in back, we have a parking lot kind of PE area.

28:41.301 --> 28:45.748
It was kind of this, almost this half the block building.

28:47.490 --> 28:53.138
We saw the growth as it went from year to year from zero to, you know, ended up in

28:53.410 --> 29:00.418
When we left around 550, I think it was, they were learning about a relationship with Christ and what that meant and who Jesus was.

29:00.538 --> 29:09.488
And we saw the results of that as the parents themselves later were being reached because they had a desire for values, but they didn't really know, have them connected to anything.

29:09.848 --> 29:15.394
And as they begin to see the connection to Jesus and to God's Word, they begin to be kind of sent one to know more.

29:15.434 --> 29:19.058
Growing up, it was kind of challenging for me because

29:19.170 --> 29:24.195
and not really to a public school where all the kids were kind of rude to me or mean to me.

29:25.016 --> 29:32.985
And there are a lot of situations in the public school that happens that does not happen in Calvary because it's where I feel loved and where I feel that I belong to.

29:33.385 --> 29:39.111
The teacher always paying attention or looking for you and taking care of you and your relationship with God.

29:39.872 --> 29:45.618
I wasn't expecting to become a teacher at first, but I would say it feels great.

29:46.242 --> 29:48.745
Pastor Robert and teacher Damadi is this school.

29:49.186 --> 29:52.590
Always taught me all these battles and about love.

29:53.211 --> 29:54.993
And is that what I wanted to teach them?

29:56.274 --> 30:08.890
Vallety is one of those examples of this same student in a different school probably wouldn't have finished, but through our school, but also personal coaching and to her life.

30:09.090 --> 30:15.378
You know, the Lord can do great things.

30:16.034 --> 30:20.259
In 2014, we got into the point we'd built the whole school, kindergarten through high school.

30:20.619 --> 30:22.381
I trained up people to kind of run it.

30:23.021 --> 30:27.406
So that was when the Lord became, made me a little restless, okay, what's next?

30:27.727 --> 30:37.237
And just through a lot of different events, once again, starting from scratch, from nothing, beginning the church, and later on beginning the lighthouse school, the second school, we started.

30:38.298 --> 30:44.404
When we left the first school that we'd built up, it was like, how are you going to leave that school and just leave it with the church?

30:45.385 --> 30:45.906
It's not.

30:45.986 --> 30:48.188
My, in a sense, legacy, it's the Lord.

30:48.249 --> 30:52.153
So I'm here to prepare it and to build it and pass it on to the next person.

30:52.814 --> 30:56.978
The Lord taught me that lesson to show me when it's time to hand something off.

30:57.779 --> 31:07.670
He gives you that peace and he also gives you this as the focus of I'm going to continue to use this and you are going to start the next step in my plan for you.

31:10.213 --> 31:11.154
It's a missionary.

31:11.458 --> 31:17.447
in this training of leaders, training of teachers, training of missionaries and pastors.

31:17.928 --> 31:20.692
That's kind of been like a third hat, I wear.

31:21.654 --> 31:27.062
One of the things we've done here in Merida is looking at all the different Calvary temples.

31:27.523 --> 31:33.151
As a church in Calvary Centro, we have kind of a direct oversight of five different missions.

31:34.153 --> 31:40.242
So we have Calvary Tabi, Cho Chola, Ochocaba, Tisbaka, Tisimin, and then also Motu,

31:43.330 --> 31:47.797
Originally, it was just like a grass, you know, palapa hut.

31:48.979 --> 31:52.945
And then actually, CCA kids came and built this.

31:53.505 --> 31:54.827
We did this for like a storage.

31:54.847 --> 32:00.756
We had like a tortilla kind of milk for the corn we used there previously.

32:01.317 --> 32:04.141
They roofed that first part and then we also roofed with them.

32:04.562 --> 32:08.408
We have a team that came down and they helped roof the second, put the roof on the second part.

32:09.169 --> 32:10.651
But this is the sanctuary right now.

32:10.671 --> 32:12.434
I mean, we've been coming here

32:12.834 --> 32:15.518
Now, let's see, 18 years.

32:16.660 --> 32:19.806
In Tabi, we have our compassionate sight.

32:20.146 --> 32:27.719
We've seen families and kids their lives have been touched when you not only bring the word, but also bring help in education and medical help.

32:27.759 --> 32:33.829
They're very much more open to listen and to do something with the message that we're given.

32:34.570 --> 32:37.134
This is our next project, the church building.

32:38.817 --> 32:39.378
We've been

32:40.802 --> 32:45.188
finishing the roof so they can actually put in, and they've been getting this ready.

32:45.208 --> 32:46.129
This is the next step.

32:46.149 --> 32:53.758
They're gonna put in the crossbars and then put the roofing, the roof on next.

32:53.778 --> 32:58.965
And after the roof, then we'll have to do work on the floors and the rest part, but the roof is on its way.

32:59.586 --> 33:00.106
Step one.

33:04.212 --> 33:09.298
When I started this journey, I had no idea of all the adventures the Lord was gonna take us on.

33:09.474 --> 33:12.419
And I can tell you, look back and say it was worth every moment.

33:12.799 --> 33:14.622
The difficult, the hard times.

33:15.123 --> 33:25.699
More than the buildings and the school and the structures that we've done, I think it's the people around us and I look at their lives that motivates us to keep going.

33:26.300 --> 33:27.922
I think that's the most important part.

33:28.023 --> 33:32.850
I do say, oh, I did two schools, planted so many churches as just numbers.

33:33.666 --> 33:46.520
But more, I can talk about this person or that person about this life or that life and the adventure of following the Lord and seeking Him and going on this journey made everything worth it.

33:47.040 --> 33:57.211
It's easy to get comfortable where we're at, but I think sometimes when we get too comfortable, the Lord is the one that kind of refocuses us and shows us there's more that I want you to do.

33:57.271 --> 34:01.836
The Lord's saying, I want you to depend on me and show you what I want you to do.

34:01.876 --> 34:03.538
Those are those difficult

34:03.842 --> 34:05.143
decisions that we have to make.

34:05.184 --> 34:19.440
And then they're not always easy, but then we see the fruit of the.

34:19.460 --> 34:25.546
Ordinary people filled with the spirit of God sent out change world.

34:26.728 --> 34:28.690
Robert and Mars, they experienced that.

34:29.218 --> 34:33.767
And I love what is, we're not just building buildings, we're building people, we're building the kingdom of God.

34:33.807 --> 34:36.392
And it's not about us, we're gonna pass it on to the next generation.

34:36.432 --> 34:46.250
And when I think about the first generation, the first 40 years of Calvary, we have received this rich legacy, not just of outreach locally, but outreach globally, this great commission.

34:46.270 --> 34:50.418
I mean, as I look back at all that's been done in the first 40 years, I see

34:50.530 --> 35:03.624
58 churches that were planted, 24 around the globe, 155 church partnerships, 30 different nations, over 100 missionaries, over $75 million invested in these local and global initiatives.

35:03.644 --> 35:07.388
And that's been given to us as a legacy from the first generation of Calvary.

35:07.408 --> 35:12.834
So can we just take a moment and celebrate the generosity and faith and courage of the men and women who have gone before us?

35:14.476 --> 35:17.439
And our prayer is God, do it again.

35:17.459 --> 35:20.242
Do it again now in this generation.

35:20.610 --> 35:27.322
because Psalm 145 says that one generation commands or tells or declares the works of God to the next.

35:27.402 --> 35:33.654
And so we want to share with you some of the stories of these global missionaries who served here for 20 plus years all over the world.

35:34.215 --> 35:39.544
And I thought, why not have you hear it through the eyes of someone who's a next generation leader?

35:40.065 --> 35:42.610
You see, because if this is just, missions is for the

35:42.722 --> 35:44.904
The parents and the grandparents and the kids don't catch it.

35:45.085 --> 35:53.674
We're going to miss a huge part, but I remember coming here and it was just normal that we would take our six-year-old sons on mission trips so they could see and experience the broken to the world.

35:53.694 --> 36:00.081
Listen, if you want your kids to have a great experience, skip Disney World this year and take them to El Salvador or Colombia or Mexico.

36:00.381 --> 36:06.507
I promise you, it will open their eyes to not just the broken to the world, but the great adventure of following Jesus.

36:06.528 --> 36:07.128
Just consider it.

36:07.208 --> 36:08.590
I'm not, this is not a Disney Haiti thing.

36:08.610 --> 36:12.594
It's just kind of an opportunity for you to consider.

36:12.866 --> 36:14.129
Samma came here and she was 15.

36:14.610 --> 36:17.357
She was immersed in this mission, let's go environment.

36:17.377 --> 36:21.106
And I want you to hear her story as she introduces our global missionaries.

36:21.367 --> 36:27.782
Samma.

36:27.802 --> 36:30.930
Good morning, Calvary.

36:31.554 --> 36:37.641
I'm here to share with you guys about the first time I remember a fire being lit in me for global missions.

36:38.142 --> 36:38.903
It was back in 2017.

36:39.924 --> 36:44.570
I wrote in my journal about wishing I could just pack up and go tell people about Jesus.

36:45.130 --> 36:49.215
But I also knew God was still preparing me, mostly because I was still in high school.

36:49.956 --> 36:54.642
Two years later, I went on my first mission trip through CCA with the Eguayos.

36:54.946 --> 37:03.435
I'll never forget the overwhelming and humbling experience of witnessing God's deep love for people in these towns and villages I would have never known.

37:03.875 --> 37:04.836
But God knew them.

37:05.777 --> 37:09.401
And that was only the start of many more trips God would take me on from then.

37:09.821 --> 37:12.204
But what I want to share with you today is not about me.

37:12.844 --> 37:16.067
It's about some men and women who I look up to as heroes in the faith.

37:16.648 --> 37:22.514
Mighty warriors for God who accepted the call to make disciples in hard to reach areas.

37:23.234 --> 37:26.239
ordinary men and women, empowered by an extraordinary God.

37:26.820 --> 37:39.661
You see, in Africa and the Middle East, our missionaries are bringing the gospel to highly persecuted and impoverished regions, and God, He is bringing revival, whether you see it or not, to people who are accepting Him despite the cost.

37:40.222 --> 37:42.546
For example, Paul and Marcia Cowley

37:42.722 --> 37:54.456
They've served in Kenya for over 20 years through the two Bible schools they started in the largest slums of Nairobi, equipping hundreds of pastors and ministry leaders, reminding them that God sees them.

37:55.297 --> 37:59.923
David and Chris Lawrence, they are training Christian leaders in the Middle East to share the gospel.

38:00.383 --> 38:07.952
They're translating biblical resources and displaying the love of Jesus tangibly in one of the least reached regions of the world.

38:08.653 --> 38:12.658
Claudia Rengo was sent from Calvary to Uganda in 1999.

38:12.930 --> 38:22.402
While serving at Good Shepherds' fold and teaching the Bible to young children, she's been a mom to hundreds over the years, while also fostering and adopting children of her own.

38:23.263 --> 38:31.173
In Europe, we have missionaries bringing the light and joy of Christ to dark places, where a post-modern culture has convinced people they don't need Jesus.

38:31.794 --> 38:34.898
Cornell and Karen Baker are just one example of this.

38:35.074 --> 38:44.465
They serve in Romania through their church and after school program, making a space for all the marginalized and forgotten Roma people to belong and grow in their faith.

38:45.346 --> 38:56.218
And all across Central and South America, we have missionaries who are planting churches, ministering to people in jails, convalescent homes, schools, and just being the hands and feet of Jesus.

38:56.699 --> 39:02.866
And some of them include Fernando Rodriguez and Diana Gomez, who serve in Cuba, the country my family's from.

39:03.266 --> 39:10.180
Despite the hardships and struggles the people face there every day, God, he has not stopped building his church.

39:11.021 --> 39:18.176
Alexander and Carolina Diaz serve on the small Colombian island of Día Rabomba, where children are highly susceptible to exploitation.

39:18.737 --> 39:25.330
Through their ministry, some of the most vulnerable children and families in the country are choosing to follow Jesus.

39:25.634 --> 39:34.025
And then Jose and Ufami Amaro, who serve in Ecuador, are bringing God's word to communities with some of the highest crime rates and much brokenness.

39:34.405 --> 39:38.090
Yet God, he has not stopped showing up to rescue and restore.

39:38.150 --> 39:46.942
And there are so many others that I can't share in this time, but the last family I want to share about is especially close to my heart, the Allegrates.

39:47.422 --> 39:50.386
Juan Sandra and their daughter, Eileen, who serve in Peru.

39:50.882 --> 39:58.353
I just got back from a trip with them in August where we witnessed God's faithfulness to their church and orphanage, their refuge of hope.

39:59.034 --> 40:07.526
Not only was I welcomed into their thriving and growing church family that they planted 12 years ago, but I witnessed God's redemptive power in the refuge.

40:08.027 --> 40:12.754
You see, Peru is one of the worst countries in the world for domestic abuse in the home.

40:13.435 --> 40:15.858
After years of opening their own homes,

40:15.938 --> 40:24.550
To children suffering abuse in their community, the community literally gifted them a property in the church's name to start an orphanage.

40:25.311 --> 40:29.617
God just kept providing in every possible roadblock he removed.

